<paragraph blockId="2.[189,1399,715,811]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rudzinski" authorityYear="1994" box="[189,399,715,741]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ascenda">
<emphasis box="[189,399,715,741]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Bradysia ascenda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described on the basis of three males from the Austrian Alps (
<bibRefCitation author="Rudzinski H. - G." box="[1194,1386,715,741]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="281 - 292" refId="ref5972" refString="Rudzinski H. - G. 1994. Neue Mitteilungen zur Trauermuckenfauna Osterreichs (Diptera Nematocera: Sciaridae). Entomofauna, Zeitschrift fur Entomologie 15: 281 - 292." type="journal article" year="1994">
Rudzinski 
<date box="[1323,1386,715,741]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1994">1994</date>
</bibRefCitation>
). In having its setae pale and in having a distinct sensory pit in the maxillary palpus, it belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[189,385,785,811]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tilicola">
<emphasis box="[189,385,785,811]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Bradysia tilicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of 
<bibRefCitation author="Menzel F. &amp; Mohrig W." box="[500,803,785,811]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 761" refId="ref5827" refString="Menzel F. &amp; Mohrig W. 2000. Revision der palaarktischen Trauermucken (Diptera: Sciaridae). Studia Dipterologica, Suppl. 6 (for 1999): 1 - 761." type="journal article" year="2000">
Menzel &amp; Mohrig (
<date box="[730,795,785,811]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2000">2000</date>
)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
